<paragraph blockId="12.[595,732,810,834]" box="[595,732,810,834]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">
(
<figureCitation box="[602,724,810,834]" captionStart-0="Figs 52–53" captionStart-1="Figs 54–60" captionStartId-0="12.[133,170,1553,1572]" captionStartId-1="13.[133,170,1252,1271]" captionTargetBox-0="[137,1156,1090,1499]" captionTargetBox-1="[137,1158,220,1229]" captionTargetId-0="figure-461@12.[610,1156,1090,1499]" captionTargetPageId-0="12" captionTargetPageId-1="13" captionText-0="Figs 52–53. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 52 – head; 53 – left face of thorax." captionText-1="Figs 54–60. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 54 – right side of scutellum; 55–57 – hypopygium; 58 – front tarsus; 59 – hind femur; 60 – wing." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252179" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252183" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6252179/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6252183/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">Figs 52–60</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[133,1154,856,1065]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">
Diagnosis (male). In the keys to British species (
<bibRefCitation author="DISNEY R. H. L." box="[745,887,856,881]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref7257" refString="DISNEY R. H. L. 1989. Scuttle Flies Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 10 (8): 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplet 150, where neither lead fits. In 
<bibRefCitation author="SCHMITZ H. &amp; DELAGE A." box="[413,708,887,911]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" pagination="665 - 712" refId="ref7586" refString="SCHMITZ H. &amp; DELAGE A. 1981. Phoridae. In: LINDNER E (ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Regi on 4 (33) (Lieferung 325): 665 - 712. Stuttgart, E. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung." type="book chapter" year="1981">Schmitz &amp; Delage’s (1981)</bibRefCitation>
keys to Abteiling VI it runs to couplet 47 lead 2, to the male attributed to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schmitz)" baseAuthorityName="Schmitz" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[518,749,918,942]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubida">
<emphasis box="[518,631,918,942]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">M. rubida</emphasis>
(Schmitz)
</taxonomicName>
by Lundbeck (1922). The latter is immediately distinguished by its brownish abdominal venter, the brown tip to the hind femur and costal section 1 being about equal to sections 2+3. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmitz" baseAuthorityYear="1918" box="[769,880,979,1003]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubida">
<emphasis box="[769,880,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">M. rubida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the female only. Its description was amplified by 
<bibRefCitation author="BUCK M. &amp; DISNEY R. H. L." box="[683,956,1010,1034]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" pagination="73 - 154" refId="ref7113" refString="BUCK M. &amp; DISNEY R. H. L. 2001. Revision of the Megaselia giraudii and M. densior species complexes of Europe, including ecological notes (Diptera, Phoridae). Beitrage zur Entomologie 51: 73 - 154." type="journal article" year="2001">Buck &amp; Disney (2001)</bibRefCitation>
. Its costal ratios correspond to those of Lundbeck’s male.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252179" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6252179" box="[133,823,1553,1572]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252179/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" startId="12.[133,170,1553,1572]" targetBox="[137,1156,1090,1499]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph blockId="12.[133,823,1553,1572]" box="[133,823,1553,1572]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">
Figs 52–53. 
<taxonomicName authority="DISNEY &amp; WINQVIST, 2018" authorityName="DISNEY &amp; WINQVIST" authorityYear="2018" box="[240,421,1553,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="necrubida" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[240,421,1553,1572]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">Megaselia necrubida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[426,473,1553,1572]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
male: 52 – head; 53 – left face of thorax.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="12.[133,1154,1603,1688]" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">
Male. (the abdomen was full of air bubbles whose expulsion caused some damage to the hypopygium). Head as 
<figureCitation box="[383,461,1633,1658]" captionStart="Figs 52–53" captionStartId="12.[133,170,1553,1572]" captionTargetBox="[137,1156,1090,1499]" captionTargetId="figure-461@12.[610,1156,1090,1499]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 52–53. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 52 – head; 53 – left face of thorax." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252179" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252179/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="23">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
, the frons having dense but very fine microtrichia. Palps yellow, with 6 bristles and fewer hairs. Labella narrow and pale. Thorax yellowish brown to brown.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252183" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6252183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252183/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" startId="13.[133,170,1252,1271]" targetBox="[137,1158,220,1229]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph blockId="13.[133,1154,1252,1296]" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">
Figs 54–60. 
<taxonomicName authority="DISNEY &amp; WINQVIST, 2018" authorityName="DISNEY &amp; WINQVIST" authorityYear="2018" box="[241,422,1252,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="necrubida" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[241,422,1252,1271]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Megaselia necrubida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[427,474,1253,1272]" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
male: 54 – right side of scutellum; 55–57 – hypopygium; 58 – front tarsus; 59 – hind femur; 60 – wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="13.[133,1155,1321,1714]" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">
The 3 notopleural bristles and bare mesopleuron as 
<figureCitation box="[725,804,1321,1345]" captionStart="Figs 52–53" captionStartId="12.[133,170,1553,1572]" captionTargetBox="[137,1156,1090,1499]" captionTargetId="figure-461@12.[610,1156,1090,1499]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figs 52–53. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 52 – head; 53 – left face of thorax." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252179" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252179/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
. Scutellum with 4 strong bristles (
<figureCitation box="[141,227,1352,1376]" captionStart="Figs 54–60" captionStartId="13.[133,170,1252,1271]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1229]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 54–60. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 54 – right side of scutellum; 55–57 – hypopygium; 58 – front tarsus; 59 – hind femur; 60 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252183/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergites brown with moderate hairs even at the rear of T6 (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1142,1352,1376]" captionStart="Figs 54–60" captionStartId="13.[133,170,1252,1271]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1229]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 54–60. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 54 – right side of scutellum; 55–57 – hypopygium; 58 – front tarsus; 59 – hind femur; 60 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252183/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
). Venter yellow and with hairs on segments 3–6. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[833,956,1382,1406]" captionStart="Figs 54–60" captionStartId="13.[133,170,1252,1271]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1229]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 54–60. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 54 – right side of scutellum; 55–57 – hypopygium; 58 – front tarsus; 59 – hind femur; 60 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252183/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Figs 55–57</figureCitation>
, with the left lobe of the hypandrium being pale and the right lobe vestigial. Legs yellow. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–5 and 5 longer than 4 (
<figureCitation box="[839,920,1443,1468]" captionStart="Figs 54–60" captionStartId="13.[133,170,1252,1271]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1229]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 54–60. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 54 – right side of scutellum; 55–57 – hypopygium; 58 – front tarsus; 59 – hind femur; 60 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252183/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.9 times its length. Hind femur as 
<figureCitation box="[808,887,1474,1498]" captionStart="Figs 54–60" captionStartId="13.[133,170,1252,1271]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1229]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 54–60. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 54 – right side of scutellum; 55–57 – hypopygium; 58 – front tarsus; 59 – hind femur; 60 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252183/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
. Hind tibia with a dozen differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[208,287,1536,1560]" captionStart="Figs 54–60" captionStartId="13.[133,170,1252,1271]" captionTargetBox="[137,1158,220,1229]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 54–60. Megaselia necrubida n. sp. male: 54 – right side of scutellum; 55–57 – hypopygium; 58 – front tarsus; 59 – hind femur; 60 – wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6252183" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6252183/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="24">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity box="[302,430,1536,1560]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="1.85" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.8">1.8–1.9 mm</quantity>
long. Costal index 0.47. Costal ratios 5.1: 3.1–3.2: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[284,380,1567,1591]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
long. No hair at base of vein 3. With 3 axillary bristles, the outer being 
<quantity box="[133,228,1597,1621]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="13" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="0.12">0.12 mm</quantity>
long. Sc reaching R1. Haltere knob yellow.
</paragraph>
